        <p>
          Erik Marutian is the founder of <strong class="text-cream">Talaxy.ai</strong>, where he applies over 15 years of enterprise technology experience to help growing companies find the right talent and automate white-collar work with AI.
        </p>

        <p>
          Before launching Talaxy, Erik founded <strong class="text-cream">Cald AI</strong>, an AI-powered communication platform that harnesses natural language processing and machine learning to make every customer interaction feel human. He also leads development at <strong class="text-cream">FlashCrafter.ai</strong>, building tools at the intersection of AI and creative workflows.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-cream !mb-3 !mt-10">Enterprise Technology Background</h2>
        <p>
          Erik's career spans some of the most demanding technology environments in financial services. As <strong class="text-cream">Head of Wealth and SME Technology</strong> at <strong class="text-cream">Bank of the West</strong>, he led digital transformation initiatives for small and medium enterprise banking, overseeing IT solutions delivery across the SME channel. Earlier, he served as a <strong class="text-cream">Senior Developer</strong> at <strong class="text-cream">Charles Schwab</strong>, specializing in identity and access management systems that secured millions of customer accounts.
        </p>

        <p>
          His expertise includes IT consulting, SaaS development, and custom software development — skills he now channels into building AI-first products for companies at the inflection point between startup agility and enterprise scale.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-cream !mb-3 !mt-10">Vision for Talaxy</h2>
        <p>
          Erik built Talaxy with a simple thesis: growing companies shouldn't have to choose between hiring great people and automating the work that slows them down. By combining AI-powered talent search with intelligent automation, Talaxy gives SMBs the same workforce advantages that enterprise companies take for granted — at a fraction of the cost and complexity.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-cream !mb-3 !mt-10">Speaker &amp; Thought Leader</h2>
        <p>
          Erik is an active speaker in the technology community. He presented at <strong class="text-cream">Decision CAMP 2014</strong> on using rules-based GUI frameworks to power dynamic financial applications, and continues to share insights on AI, fintech, and workforce automation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-xl text-cream !mb-3 !mt-10">Education</h2>
        <p>
          Erik holds a <strong class="text-cream">B.S. in Managerial Economics</strong> from the <strong class="text-cream">University of California, Davis</strong>.
